ssageRole.ASSISTANT: 'assistant'>, additional_kwargs={}, blocks=[TextBlock(block_type='text', text='{\n    "reasoning": "The simulation is failing because the current implementation does not correctly handle the transition between states based on the input conditions. Specifically, the `next_state` is being updated to `WALK_RIGHT` when either `bump_left` is high or `bump_right` is high, regardless of the combination of both. This leads to incorrect behavior in the simulation.",\n    "action_input": {\n        "command": "replace_content_by_matching",\n        "args": {\n            "old_content": "                    next_state = WALK_RIGHT;",\n            "new_content": "                    next_state = WALK_RIGHT;"\n        }\n    }\n}')]), ChatMessage(role=<MessageRole.USER: 'user'>, additional_kwargs={}, blocks=[TextBlock(block_type='text', text='\nOutput after running given action:\n<action_output>\n{\n    "is_action_executed": true,\n    "is_syntax_pass": true,\n    "is_sim_pass": false,\n    "error_msg": "{\\n    \\"stdout\\": \\"VCD info: dumpfile wave.vcd opened for output.\\\\nHint: Your reset should be asynchronous, but doesn\'t appear to be.\\\\n./output_t22c_qwen25coder7b_shard4_0/VERILOG_EVAL_V2_Prob127_lemmings1/tb.sv:59: $finish called at 1146 (1ps)\\\\nHint: Output \'walk_left\' has 16 mismatches. First mismatch occurred at time 55.\\\\nHint: Output \'walk_right\' has 16 mismatches. First mismatch occurred at time 55.\\\\nHint: Total mismatched samples is 16 out of 229 samples\\\\n\\\\nSimulation finished at 1146 ps\\\\nMismatches: 16 in 229 samples\\\\n\\",\\n    \\"stderr\\": \\"\\"\\n}",\n    "sim_mismatch_cnt": 16\n}\n</action_output>\n')]), ChatMessage(role=<MessageRole.USER: 'user'>, additional_kwargs={}, blocks=[TextBlock(block_type='text', text='\nYour response will be processed by a program, not human.\nSo, please STRICTLY FOLLOW the output format given as XML tag content below to generate a VALID JSON OBJECT:\n<output_format>\n{\n    "reas